{
  "doc_id": "55047",
  "text": "Herbaspirillum seropedicae is a nitrogen-fixing b-proteobacterium associated with important agricultural Gramineae, such as rice, wheat, sorghum, and sugarcane [CITATION_1] . Transcriptional control of nitrogen fixation in H. seropedicae relies on a NifL-independent NifA system that is controlled by both nitrogen and oxygen levels [CITATION_2] .",
